main event: A witness reported seeing a twinkling point of light in West Carrollton, Ohio on August 20, 1963 around 11:30 PM.
interesting points: The witness observed the phenomenon for approximately 1 hour.
The sighting was classified as a 'ground-visual' type of observation.
The report states there were 'insufficient data for evaluation' in regards to the observed object.
The witness was questioned about their background and whether they had seen similar phenomena before.
The report includes a diagram for the witness to sketch the location and movement of the observed object.
